Best thing I liked was the quiet - someone was smart enough to add design features to minimize noise - ice machines are in a separate room, doors do not slam, modified layout (no long corridors).	Large, clean rooms, super-comfortable beds, no issues with noise, great climate control system, clean, safe garage.	It is very noisy: the room windows do not have sufficient glazing to keep out street noise and the rooms have very thin walls.	Finally, at the end of the day, we enjoyed a very quiet and relaxing room - we could barely believe we were downtown.